ShortDescription: Unisex Anti Blue Light Protective Computer Screen Glasses
LongDescription:
We live totally surrounded by screens, spending almost nine hours a day, on average, in front of digital devices. All these devices emit blue light, and since our eyes aren't protected against this overexposure, the light can be detrimental.
WHAT IS BLUE LIGHT?Blue light is a harmful portion of light emitted by digital screens. According to the Paris Vision Institute, younger people exposed to an excess amount of blue light can start to experience age-related macular degeneration at an earlier stage. Other research states that excess exposure is also the leading cause of vision loss for people over 50.

HOW TO PROTECT YOUR EYESBlue light blocking glasses from our store are specially designed to filter out harmful blue-violet light. This makes screen time more comfortable and help eliminate symptoms of digital eyestrain. Simultaneously, this Blu-ray filter glasses will improve your sleep and make you fall asleep.

ShortDescription: Photochromic Sunglasses With Polarized Lens Anti Glare Driver Sunglasses
LongDescription:
Our sunglasses are made of special photochromic polarized lenses. When driving at night or into a dark environment, the lenses are lightcolored transparent to enhancing the visibility while effectively reducing the glare. During the daytime, it can effectively filter the strong light, enhance the visual sharpness, reduce eyes fatigue, and keep the eyes always in the most comfortable state of outdoor activities.

Light Grey Glasses (Photochromic)

Photochromic Technology

This type of lens features a substantial photochromic effect. It is not totally transparent, and its color also changes according to how much it absorbs UV rays (ultraviolet radiation).

Photochromic lenses change in color under different light conditions. They darken when exposed to strong sunlight, which can effectively protect your eyes from over-exposure. Our photochromic lenses will change in color only when exposed to UV rays, which means the lenses won’t change colour while you’re inside of your car or somewhere there are no UV rays.

The photochromic lenses detect the intensity of light change and absorb ultraviolet rays automatically. When exposed to intenser sunlight, they will turn darker and at the same time they offer ultimate blockage against UV rays to keep your eyes comfortable by helping you see more clearly and relieving eye strain.

At night or in dark tunnels, these lenses will become clear again very quick, providing sharper vision and longer sight distance for your eyes to see the surroundings clearly.
